.\" Man page for one-click
.TH ONE-CLICK 8 "@DATE@" "One-Click v@VERSION@" "One-Click Manual"

.SH NAME
one-click \- Modular server management, security auditing, and disaster recovery toolkit

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B one-click
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fISUBCOMMANDS\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B one-click
is a high-performance, modular toolkit designed for predictable and auditable Linux system administration. It specializes in automated deployments, natural-language security management, and "bare-metal" style recovery.

.PP
Key architectural features include:
.IP \(bu 2
.B Resilience:
Long-running operations execute within a 
.BR tmux (1)
session to ensure persistence against SSH disconnects.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Safety:
Destructive operations (reinstall, migrate) require explicit confirmation and hardware-level validation.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Isolation:
Web services and installers run in dedicated system slices and secured user environments.

.PP
The toolkit is suitable for VPS, dedicated servers, and bare-metal systems. Operations may be interactive or fully automated.

.PP
All commands are explicit and user-initiated. Destructive operations require confirmation to protect system integrity.

.SH SECURITY & AUDITING

.SS IDS (Intrusion Detection System)
The built-in IDS monitors integrity of system binaries and critical directories (e.g., /bin, /sbin, /etc). 
.IP \(bu 2
.B Baseline:
Creates a cryptographically signed snapshot of the "clean" system state on first execution.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Monitoring:
Subsequent scans compare the live system against the baseline to detect unauthorized modifications, file replacements, or malware persistence.

.SS Security Audits
Provides deep inspection of the server, including active socket analysis, process tree validation, and reputation lookups for active connections via external intelligence APIs.

.SH RULE-ENGINE (Firewall Management)
The 
.B rule-engine
is a human-parsable wrapper for 
.B iptables 
and 
.B nftables.
It allows administrators to manage firewalls in natural language while maintaining extreme safety.

.SS Triple-Layer Lockout Protection
Prevents accidental remote lockout using three layers:
.IP "1. Visual Guard:"
Displays a clear summary of translated commands and affected ports before execution.
.IP "2. Namespace Dry-Run:"
Spawns an isolated network namespace, clones the current firewall state, and tests new rules against simulated critical services (SSH, DNS, Web) before modifying production.
.IP "3. Auto-Rollback (Transactional Commit):"
After applying live rules, the system enters a "Pending" state. The user has 
.B 15 seconds
to confirm connectivity. If no confirmation occurs, the previous configuration is automatically restored.

.SH WORDPRESS & WEB INSTALLER
The WordPress module implements a "Site-as-a-Container" approach without Docker overhead.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Resource Isolation:
Each site runs under its own Linux user and PHP-FPM pool.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Systemd Slices:
CPU and RAM limits are enforced per site via systemd slices.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Automated Backups:
Supports local snapshots and remote off-site rsync/rclone scheduling per domain.

