.SH WORDPRESS
The
.B one-click
tool includes a built-in WordPress automation module for unattended or guided site deployment. This module handles webserver configuration, database setup, optional caching, and SSL certificate provisioning.

.PP
Before using these commands, ensure DNS A records for both the root domain and the www subdomain point to this server’s IP.

.PP
WordPress sites installed via
.B one-click
are located under:
.RS
/etc/one-click/wordpress/<domain>/www
.RE
Databases are dynamically named based on the site and user.

.SH WORDPRESS COMMANDS
Usage:

.RS
.B one-click --wp-create
.RE

Installs a new WordPress site interactively. Prompts for:

.IP \(bu 2
Domain name (validated with regex)

.IP \(bu 2
Site title

.IP \(bu 2
Admin username and password (enforced minimum complexity)

.IP \(bu 2
Admin email

.IP \(bu 2
Database username and password

.IP \(bu 2
Webserver choice (Nginx or Apache)

.IP \(bu 2
Optional Redis plugin activation

.PP
Installer actions:

.IP \(bu 2
Install required packages (webserver, PHP, MariaDB, certbot, etc.)

.IP \(bu 2
Configure selected webserver with document root and virtual host

.IP \(bu 2
Create database and user (or reuse existing)

.IP \(bu 2
Download and configure WordPress via WP‑CLI

.IP \(bu 2
Optionally install plugins including caching and security tools

.IP \(bu 2
Attempt Let's Encrypt SSL provisioning and update WordPress URLs

.PP
If SSL provisioning fails, users can retry, skip, or modify options.

.RS
.B one-click --wp-ssl <domain>
.RE

Ensures SSL is provisioned for an existing WordPress site:

.IP \(bu 2
Validates DNS for domain and www subdomain

.IP \(bu 2
Invokes Certbot to issue or renew certificate

.IP \(bu 2
Reloads configured webserver

.IP \(bu 2
Updates WordPress URLs to HTTPS if successful

.PP
If DNS or Certbot fails, options are provided to retry, change contact email, view logs, or skip.

.SH EXAMPLES
Install a new WordPress site:
.RS
.B one-click --wp-create
.RE

Provision SSL for existing site:
.RS
.B one-click --wp-ssl example.com
.RE

.SH NOTES
WordPress site files:
.RS
/etc/one-click/wordpress/www/<domain>
.RE

Backups:
.RS
/etc/one-click/wordpress/backups/<domain>
.RE

SSL certificates managed by Certbot:
.RS
/etc/letsencrypt/live/<domain>
.RE

.PP
Domains must resolve to this server before SSL issuance.

.SH RULE-ENGINE
The
.B rule-engine
module provides natural-language firewall management within
.B one-click.

.PP
It allows administrators to construct human-readable firewall rules, which are automatically translated into valid commands for the active firewall backend (supported: iptables/ip6tables, nftables).

.PP
Firewall changes use a staged commit process with automatic rollback. A
.B 10-second verification timer
ensures that changes are reverted if confirmation is not received.

.SH RULE-ENGINE FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
Human-readable firewall parsing

.IP \(bu 2
Support for TCP, UDP, ICMP, and multiport rules

.IP \(bu 2
Source and destination filtering via IPv4, IPv6, and CIDR ranges

.IP \(bu 2
Service-name to port mapping (e.g., ssh → 22)

.IP \(bu 2
Automatic firewall backend detection

.IP \(bu 2
Natural language and raw command chaining

.IP \(bu 2
Firewall rule alias system for IP groups

.IP \(bu 2
Sensitive port protection

.IP \(bu 2
Dry-run preview mode (--dry-run)

.IP \(bu 2
Audit mode for rule inspection

.IP \(bu 2
Full firewall backup and restore

.IP \(bu 2
Transactional commit with rollback protection

